reviews.text: Long wait for a table on Sundays. Clean environment, hardworking staff. Food is okay. Prices are reasonable.

Food good
Service normal
Hygiene good
price good

The three of us had lunch. They offered a lunch set of fried noodles/rice/rice noodles, half a chicken, vegetables in soup, three dim sums and mango pudding. For $188 (+$20 on Sat & Sun). Good value for this lot but fried noodles and chicken tasted rather bland. We also ordered har gau, fried beancurd sheet rolls, fried dough wrapped in rice rolls, chicken and taro wrapped in beancurd sheets and tripes. Bill came to $324. Good value but I can't score them more than three stars considering most items lacked flavour.
